/* 
open cmd in the project folder and run the following command
 npm init 
 then initializ properties of the project

create sturcture of the project as follows
 model folder
 controller folder
 route folder
 index.js file
 then create all model files in model folder

 then open terminal and install dependencies
    npm install express - as it is a web framework for nodejs
    npm install mongoose - as it is a mongodb object modeling tool(mapper)
    npm install body-parser - as it is a middleware to parse incoming request bodies
    npm install nodemon - as it is a tool that helps develop node.js based applications by automatically restarting the node application when file changes in the directory are detected
    npm install dotenv - as it is a zero-dependency module that loads environment variables from a .env file into process.env
    npm install jsonwebtoken - as it is a compact, URL-safe means of representing claims to be transferred between two parties (security)
    npm install bcryptjs - as it is a library to help you hash passwords (security)
    all in one : npm install express mongoose body-parser nodemon dotenv jsonwebtoken bcryptjs 

    then create a .env file 
    create controllers and route files
    

*/